    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are looking for a high-ceiling performance today, led by **Kyle Tucker**, who enters with our highest daily efficiency score of 74.43. Despite a slight park penalty, **Kyle Tucker** benefits from a massive 10% boost due to a favorable matchup against May and a 5% wind-aided cushion, cementing his status as the primary engine of our lineup. **Drake Baldwin** (70.94) and **Sam Antonacci** (64.32) provide secondary firepower; **Drake Baldwin** is particularly well-positioned in the #2 hole with a 14% park bump, while **Sam Antonacci** capitalizes on an excellent 0.379 xwOBA and an aggressive #1 spot to exploit a favorable matchup against Canning. **Josh Lowe** (64.52) rounds out our elite-tier threats, though we are closely monitoring the 53% SB-hold rate of the opposing backstop, which may temper his stolen base upside despite his dynamic platoon advantage.\n\nThe bench decision for **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (51.19) was the most difficult, as his strong raw base projection and solid xwOBA of 0.386 were ultimately negated by a tough matchup against Ryan. We opted for the efficiency of **Jackson Merrill** (60.32) and **Andy Pages** (58.22) instead, betting on their respective matchup contexts over the pedigree of **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** against a formidable arm. Risks remain, most notably with **Josh Jung**, whose score of 55.04 is contingent on a pending lineup confirmation at the #3 spot. Additionally, while we like the upside for **Coby Mayo** (53.39) thanks to wind conditions and a platoon edge, his matchup against Fried is a volatility point, and we must navigate the 54% SB-hold rate of the opposing catcher which suppresses his aggressive base-running profile. We are proceeding with caution on **Heliot Ramos**, whose 50.58 score is dragged down by a -6% park factor, but his leadoff role keeps him firmly in the mix for R and SB volume.",
